The paper deals with the complexity of learning neural networks, which is a central topic in machine learning. The paper discusses lower bounds for learning one-hidden-layer neural networks with smooth activation functions, which is a problem in the field of computational learning theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the role of information theory in the analysis, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the structure of the neural network, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of statistical query algorithms, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category.
